     <div type="poem" subtype="on_frontispiece">
   <pb facs="1"/>
   <head>The Inventors premedita<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tion
upon this Emblematicall Fron<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tispice
of the subsequent pious
MEDITATIONS.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>MY Heart a matter good indite,</l>
      <l>By good Examples Cloud by Day,</l>
      <l>By Faiths shining Lamp led by Night,</l>
      <l>With Zeals wings soare up the steep way</l>
      <l>To Light inaccessible, which</l>
      <l>To Fill, and not be Fill'd, is rich.</l>
      <l>Leaving th' Earth and TITLES below,</l>
      <l>Where black Heart buried, yet not dead,</l>
      <l>Some Posthume rayes doth now bestow,</l>
      <l>Whiles it lies sleeping in Deaths bed.</l>
      <l>An Adamantine heart GOD leaves,</l>
      <l>But takes that which Contrition cleaves.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Let each sound heart take in good part</l>
      <l>This, thus reflected, Broken heart.</l>
   </lg>
